<p>I currently working on a ColdFusion (CF) project adding features to our employee appreciation award web app.</p>  <p>The problem I am having is how to keep the cfselect value when returning to the web page where it was selected.</p>  <p>Currently the nomination.cfm populates #1 drop down menu with the sub-departments names, and that is called from nomination.cfc cffunction getDept. Once that is selected then "department" passed to nomination.cfc cffunction getEmp as a cfargument.</p>  <pre><code>1. Select the location where your nominee works:  &lt;cfselect name="department" bind="cfc:nominee.getDept ()" bindonload="true" /&gt;  2. Select the nominee from the list below &lt;cfselect name="employee" bind="cfc:nominee.getEmp ({department})" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>All this code is inside a cfform where is it submitted to summary.cfm. In summary.cfm there's an edit button that goes back to the nomination.cfm. I used </p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="button" value="    Edit   " onclick="history.go(-1);"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But #1 and #2 did not kept its selected values, instead defaulted to the original drop down menu listing. I read in docs that cfc binding can not do "selected", so I am at a loss. Thanks in advance for your help!!</p>  <p>Here below is the nomination.cfc codes: </p>  <pre><code>    &lt;!--- Get array of media types ---&gt;     &lt;cffunction name="getDept" access="remote" returnType="array"&gt;          &lt;!--- Define variables ---&gt;         &lt;cfset var data=""&gt;         &lt;cfset var result=ArrayNew(2)&gt;         &lt;cfset var i=0&gt;               &lt;!--- Get data ---&gt;         &lt;cfquery name="data" datasource="HatsOff"&gt;         SELECT account_number, account_title         FROM departments         &lt;cfif session.vdept is not "All" and session.vdept is not "Letter"&gt;         WHERE [departmentname] = '#session.vdept#'           &lt;/cfif&gt;         ORDER BY account_title         &lt;/cfquery&gt;          &lt;!--- Convert results to array ---&gt;         &lt;cfloop index="i" from="1" to="#data.RecordCount#"&gt;             &lt;cfset result[i][1]=data.account_number[i]&gt;             &lt;cfset result[i][2]=data.account_title[i]&gt;         &lt;/cfloop&gt;          &lt;!--- And return it ---&gt;         &lt;cfreturn result&gt;     &lt;/cffunction&gt;      &lt;!--- Get art by media type ---&gt;     &lt;cffunction name="getEmp" access="remote" returnType="array"&gt;         &lt;cfargument name="department" type="string" required="true"&gt;          &lt;!--- Define variables ---&gt;         &lt;cfset var data=""&gt;         &lt;cfset var result=ArrayNew(2)&gt;         &lt;cfset var i=0&gt;          &lt;!--- Get data ---&gt;         &lt;cfquery name="data" datasource="HatsOff"&gt;         SELECT emp_id, emp_full_name         FROM employees         WHERE account_number = '#ARGUMENTS.department#'         ORDER BY emp_full_name         &lt;/cfquery&gt;          &lt;!--- Convert results to array ---&gt;         &lt;cfloop index="i" from="1" to="#data.RecordCount#"&gt;             &lt;cfset result[i][1]=data.emp_id[i]&gt;             &lt;cfset result[i][2]=data.emp_full_name[i]&gt;         &lt;/cfloop&gt;          &lt;!--- And return it ---&gt;         &lt;cfreturn result&gt;     &lt;/cffunction&gt;  &lt;/cfcomponent&gt; </code></pre>